Data and catalogs
-----------------

Hi-net waveform HDF5 inputs
  The Hi-net HDF5 waveform archive used for the analysis was converted from
  WIN/WIN32 seismic data with:

    Nishida, K. (2026). win32conv: A modern C implementation of WIN/WIN32
    seismic data conversion tools (Version 1.0.0) [Software].
    https://github.com/qnishida/win32conv.
    https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19879657

  The converted HDF5 waveform archive is an external input and is not
  distributed as part of this source repository.

Global CMT
    The Global Centroid Moment Tensor catalog is not distributed under the
    Autofocusing software license. Raw Global CMT catalog files and CMT catalogs
    converted for use with Autofocusing should be obtained or generated
    separately.
    Users should cite Global CMT following the guidance at:

    https://www.globalcmt.org/CMTcite.html

  The conversion helper in Scripts/GlobalCMT/ is part of this repository,
  but Global CMT data products generated by that helper are not.

vel_Nishida2008.dat
  This station-correction velocity model is derived from:

    Nishida, K., Kawakatsu, H., & Obara, K. (2008).
    Three-dimensional crustal S wave velocity structure in Japan using
    microseismic data recorded by Hi-net tiltmeters. Journal of Geophysical
    Research, 113(B10), B10302. https://doi.org/10.1029/2007JB005395

  Keep this file in the repository root when running the executables from
  this directory.

